        <!-- Section 6.3: Test Statistics -->
        <div class="section fade-in" id="test-statistics">
            <h2 class="section-title">üìä 6.3 Test Statistics and Critical Regions</h2>
            <div class="section-content">
                <div class="math-definition">
                    <h4>Test Statistic</h4>
                    <p>A <strong>test statistic</strong> $T$ is a function of sample data used to make decisions about $H_0$.</p>
                    <div class="math-formula">
                        $T = T(X_1, X_2, \ldots, X_n)$
                    </div>
                    <p><strong>Properties:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Distribution under $H_0$ is known</li>
                        <li>Large values (or small values) provide evidence against $H_0$</li>
                        <li>Used to determine critical regions</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="math-definition">
                    <h4>Critical Region</h4>
                    <p>The <strong>critical region (rejection region)</strong> $C$ is the set of test statistic values that lead to rejection of $H_0$.</p>
                    <div class="math-formula">
                        $P(T \in C | H_0 \text{ true}) = \alpha$
                    </div>
                    <p><strong>Decision Rule:</strong> Reject $H_0$ if $T \in C$</p>
                </div>

                <div class="rejection-region">
                    <h4>Critical Region Visualization</h4>
                    <p>üìà <em>Visual demonstration would show normal curve with shaded rejection regions</em></p>
                    <p>Two-tailed: Œ±/2 in each tail | One-tailed: Œ± in one tail</p>
                </div>

                <div class="example-box">
                    <h4>Example 6.3: Z-test for Mean</h4>
                    <p><strong>Setup:</strong> $H_0: \mu = \mu_0$ vs. $H_1: \mu \neq \mu_0$, $\sigma$ known</p>
                    <p><strong>Test Statistic:</strong> $Z = \frac{\bar{X} - \mu_0}{\sigma/\sqrt{n}}$</p>
                    <p><strong>Under $H_0$:</strong> $Z \sim N(0,1)$</p>
                    <p><strong>Critical Region:</strong> $|Z| > z_{\alpha/2}$ (for $\alpha = 0.05$: $|Z| > 1.96$)</p>
                    <p><strong>Decision:</strong> Reject $H_0$ if $|z_{obs}| > 1.96$</p>
                </div>

                <div class="theorem-box">
                    <h4>Common Test Statistics</h4>
                    <table class="test-statistics-table">
                        <tr>
                            <th>Parameter</th>
                            <th>Test Statistic</th>
                            <th>Distribution under $H_0$</th>
                            <th>Assumptions</th>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Mean (œÉ known)</td>
                            <td>$Z = \frac{\bar{X} - \mu_0}{\sigma/\sqrt{n}}$</td>
                            <td>$N(0,1)$</td>
                            <td>Normal or large n</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Mean (œÉ unknown)</td>
                            <td>$T = \frac{\bar{X} - \mu_0}{S/\sqrt{n}}$</td>
                            <td>$t_{n-1}$</td>
                            <td>Normal population</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Variance</td>
                            <td>$\chi^2 = \frac{(n-1)S^2}{\sigma_0^2}$</td>
                            <td>$\chi^2_{n-1}$</td>
                            <td>Normal population</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Proportion</td>
                            <td>$Z = \frac{\hat{p} - p_0}{\sqrt{p_0(1-p_0)/n}}$</td>
                            <td>$N(0,1)$</td>
                            <td>Large n</td>
                        </tr>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>

