        <!-- Section 6.5: One-Sample Tests -->
        <div class="section fade-in" id="one-sample">
            <h2 class="section-title">üéØ 6.5 Common One-Sample Tests</h2>
            <div class="section-content">
                <div class="math-definition">
                    <h4>One-Sample t-test for Mean</h4>
                    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Test hypotheses about population mean when œÉ is unknown</p>
                    <p><strong>Assumptions:</strong> Normal population or large sample</p>
                    <p><strong>Test Statistic:</strong> $t = \frac{\bar{X} - \mu_0}{S/\sqrt{n}} \sim t_{n-1}$ under $H_0$</p>
                    <p><strong>Example:</strong> $H_0: \mu = 50$ vs. $H_1: \mu \neq 50$</p>
                </div>

                <div class="math-definition">
                    <h4>One-Sample Test for Proportion</h4>
                    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Test hypotheses about population proportion</p>
                    <p><strong>Assumptions:</strong> Large sample (np‚ÇÄ ‚â• 5, n(1-p‚ÇÄ) ‚â• 5)</p>
                    <p><strong>Test Statistic:</strong> $Z = \frac{\hat{p} - p_0}{\sqrt{p_0(1-p_0)/n}} \sim N(0,1)$ under $H_0$</p>
                    <p><strong>Example:</strong> $H_0: p = 0.5$ vs. $H_1: p \neq 0.5$</p>
                </div>

                <div class="example-box">
                    <h4>Example 6.5: Weight Loss Program</h4>
                    <p><strong>Claim:</strong> Program leads to average weight loss of 10 pounds</p>
                    <p><strong>Sample:</strong> 16 participants, $\bar{x} = 12.5$ pounds, $s = 4.2$ pounds</p>
                    <p><strong>Hypotheses:</strong> $H_0: \mu = 10$ vs. $H_1: \mu > 10$ (one-tailed)</p>
                    <p><strong>Test Statistic:</strong> $t = \frac{12.5 - 10}{4.2/\sqrt{16}} = \frac{2.5}{1.05} = 2.38$</p>
                    <p><strong>p-value:</strong> $P(t_{15} > 2.38) \approx 0.015$</p>
                    <p><strong>Conclusion:</strong> Reject $H_0$ at Œ± = 0.05; evidence supports the claim</p>
                </div>

                <div class="theorem-box">
                    <h4>Test Selection Guidelines</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>One-sample t-test:</strong> Unknown œÉ, normal population or n ‚â• 30</li>
                        <li><strong>One-sample z-test:</strong> Known œÉ, normal population or n ‚â• 30</li>
                        <li><strong>Proportion test:</strong> Binomial data with large sample</li>
                        <li><strong>Chi-square test:</strong> Variance test with normal population</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

