                hint: "Think about comparing likelihoods under different hypotheses",
                explanation: "LRT compares the likelihood under H‚ÇÄ to the likelihood under H‚ÇÅ using the ratio L(H‚ÇÄ)/L(H‚ÇÅ).",
                steps: `<div class="step-title">Likelihood Ratio Test:</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <ol>
                                <li><strong>Ratio:</strong> LR = L(Œ∏‚ÇÄ)/L(Œ∏ÃÇ)</li>
                                <li><strong>L(Œ∏‚ÇÄ):</strong> Likelihood under H‚ÇÄ</li>
                                <li><strong>L(Œ∏ÃÇ):</strong> Maximum likelihood (unrestricted)</li>
