                hint: "Think about the asymptotic distribution of the likelihood ratio test statistic",
                explanation: "Wilks' theorem states that -2 log(LR) asymptotically follows a œá¬≤ distribution under H‚ÇÄ.",
                steps: `<div class="step-title">Wilks' Theorem:</div>
                        <div class="step-content">
                            <ol>
                                <li><strong>Test statistic:</strong> Œõ = -2 log(LR)</li>
                                <li><strong>Distribution:</strong> Œõ ~ œá¬≤(df) under H‚ÇÄ</li>
